import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='lon', y='lat', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude across all state capitals?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    state_counts = data['state'].value_counts().reset_index()
    state_counts.columns = ['state', 'count']
    chart = sns.barplot(x='state', y='count', data=state_counts)
    plt.title('Which state has the highest number of state capitals?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
from scipy.spatial.distance import pdist, squareform

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Calculate pairwise distances between state capitals
    distances = pdist(data[['lat', 'lon']].values)
    distances = squareform(distances)

    # Flatten the distance matrix and remove duplicates
    unique_distances = np.unique(distances[np.triu_indices(len(distances), k=1)])

    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(unique_distances, bins=20, kde=True)
    plt.xlabel("Distance between state capitals")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of distance between state capitals?", wrap=True)

    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
